subSection.paragraph:
The genus
Homogryllacris Liu, 2007
currently comprises 27 species, which are distributed in China , India and Southeast Asia ( Liu, 2007 ;
Shi et al ., 2012
;
Du et al ., 2016
; Ingrisch, 2018 ;
Li et al ., 2019
;
Bian et al ., 2021
; Liu et al ., 2021; Liu et al ., 2021;
Lu et al ., 2022
;
Duan et al ., 2023
; Zhang et al ., 2023; Zhang et al ., 2023;
Pang et al ., 2023a
, 2023b ). This genus is characterized by male ninth abdominal tergite being without process, tenth abdominal tergite is very short, and the middle of posterior margin has a pair of posterior processes, ovipositor is longer than hind femur, almost straight. As an interesting group, some species of this genus are fully winged, brachypterous and micropterous species also occur.

With its unique natural geographic location and complex and diverse climatic conditions, Xizang is rich in animal and plant resources, it has long been reputed as a rare “green gene pool” and “natural museum” in the world. In recent years, many new species of Ensifera were reported from Xizang by Chinese scholars (Wang et al. , 2012; Wang et al. , 2012;
Jiao et al. , 2013
;
Wang et al ., 2014
;
Chang et al ., 2016
;
Shi et al ., 2016
; Wu & Liu, 2017 ; Ma, 2018 ; Wang & Liu, 2018 ; Wu & Liu, 2018 ;
Ma et al ., 2021
; Wu & Liu, 2023 ).

